# 1. CAN Oscilloscope Interpretation Guide (Real Waveform Analysis)

## A. Healthy CAN Waveform (Baseline Reference)

| Parameter            | CAN High (CAN_H)  | CAN Low (CAN_L)   | Interpretation              |
| -------------------- | ----------------- | ----------------- | --------------------------- |
| Idle level           | ~2.5 V flat       | ~2.5 V flat       | Bus idle (recessive state)  |
| Dominant bit         | ~3.5 V pulses     | ~1.5 V pulses     | Data transmission active    |
| Differential voltage | ~2.0 V            | inverse           | Strong, clean communication |
| Edge shape           | Sharp square wave | Sharp square wave | Proper termination          |
| Noise level          | Minimal           | Minimal           | Good shielding & grounding  |

### Key Oscilloscope Signature

| Feature               | Meaning                       |
| --------------------- | ----------------------------- |
| Symmetrical waveforms | Balanced CAN_H and CAN_L      |
| Constant 2V swing     | Proper bus bias               |
| No ringing            | Correct termination (120Ω x2) |

---

## B. Fault Waveform Interpretation

| Fault Condition           | CAN_H Waveform      | CAN_L Waveform    | Oscilloscope Clue    | Root Cause                |
| ------------------------- | ------------------- | ----------------- | -------------------- | ------------------------- |
| Open CAN_H wire           | Flat ~2.5 V         | Normal waveform   | Missing upper swing  | Broken harness            |
| Open CAN_L wire           | Normal              | Flat ~2.5 V       | Missing lower swing  | Connector fault           |
| Short CAN_H to GND        | ~0 V                | ~2.5 V            | No differential      | Ground short              |
| Short CAN_L to GND        | ~2.5 V              | ~0 V              | Distorted signal     | Ground fault              |
| No termination            | Ringing / overshoot | Same              | Oscillation at edges | Missing 120Ω resistor     |
| Weak battery/voltage drop | Reduced amplitude   | Reduced amplitude | Low swing (~1V)      | Power supply issue        |
| EMI noise                 | Jagged waveform     | Jagged waveform   | Random spikes        | Ignition/alternator noise |

---

## C. Oscilloscope Time Domain Interpretation

| Setting       | Recommended Value            | Purpose                    |
| ------------- | ---------------------------- | -------------------------- |
| Time base     | 50 µs – 500 µs/div           | View multiple bits         |
| Voltage scale | 1–2 V/div                    | Capture differential swing |
| Trigger       | CAN_L or CAN_H edge          | Stabilize waveform         |
| Probe type    | Differential probe preferred | Avoid ground loops         |

