# 2. Step-by-Step “No Communication” Troubleshooting Tree

## A. Logical Diagnostic Flow

| Step | Action                           | Tool            | Expected Result  | If Failed → Cause             |
| ---- | -------------------------------- | --------------- | ---------------- | ----------------------------- |
| 1    | Check ignition + battery voltage | Multimeter      | >12 V            | Low battery / ECU not powered |
| 2    | Scan OBD-II                      | Scanner         | ECU list visible | Gateway or bus failure        |
| 3    | Check CAN resistance (IGN OFF)   | Multimeter      | ~60 Ω            | Termination fault             |
| 4    | Check CAN voltage (IGN ON)       | Multimeter      | ~2.5 V idle      | Short/open fault              |
| 5    | Isolate network sections         | Disconnect ECUs | Bus recovers?    | Faulty ECU found              |
| 6    | Oscilloscope test                | Scope           | Clean waveform   | Noise/wiring issue            |
| 7    | Check fuses & grounds            | Visual + meter  | All OK           | Power/ground failure          |
| 8    | Check gateway ECU                | Diagnostic scan | Response         | Gateway failure               |

---

## B. Quick Decision Tree (No Communication)

| Symptom                     | Most Likely Cause             |
| --------------------------- | ----------------------------- |
| No ECU communication at all | Power or CAN backbone failure |
| One ECU missing             | ECU internal fault            |
| Multiple ECUs missing       | CAN bus short/open            |
| Intermittent communication  | Loose connector / corrosion   |
| Scanner cannot connect      | Gateway or OBD wiring fault   |

---

## C. Fast Isolation Method (Pro Technician Trick)

| Step                                     | Method                       | Interpretation                         |
| ---------------------------------------- | ---------------------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| Disconnect ECUs one by one               | Remove modules from CAN line | Bus recovers → last removed ECU faulty |
| Divide CAN backbone                      | Split harness physically     | Fault localized to section             |
| Measure resistance after each disconnect | Multimeter                   | Identify shorted segment               |

