# 3. CAN vs CAN FD Differences (Modern Automotive Networks)

| Feature           | Classical CAN    | CAN FD                                  |
| ----------------- | ---------------- | --------------------------------------- |
| Max data rate     | 1 Mbps           | Up to 8 Mbps                            |
| Payload size      | 8 bytes          | Up to 64 bytes                          |
| Frame format      | Fixed length     | Flexible Data Rate                      |
| Arbitration speed | 1 Mbps           | 1 Mbps (arbitration), faster data phase |
| Efficiency        | Lower            | Higher (less overhead)                  |
| ECU requirements  | Older ECUs       | Modern ECUs                             |
| Diagnostics       | Standard OBD     | Enhanced diagnostics                    |
| Error handling    | Standard CRC     | Stronger CRC + improved detection       |
| Use cases         | Engine, ABS, BCM | ADAS, radar, cameras                    |

---

## CAN FD Key Concept

| Phase             | Speed    | Function                    |
| ----------------- | -------- | --------------------------- |
| Arbitration phase | 1 Mbps   | Message priority decision   |
| Data phase        | 2–8 Mbps | High-speed payload transfer |

---

## Why CAN FD exists

| Problem in CAN    | CAN FD Solution  |
| ----------------- | ---------------- |
| Too slow for ADAS | Higher bandwidth |
| Small payload     | 64-byte frames   |
| Too many frames   | Reduced bus load |

