# 4. Practical Car Case Studies (Real Diagnostic Scenarios)

---

## Case Study 1: Maruti Suzuki (Body CAN Failure)

| Parameter    | Details                                 |
| ------------ | --------------------------------------- |
| Vehicle type | Hatchback (body + powertrain CAN split) |
| Complaint    | Power windows + cluster dead            |
| Scan result  | U0140 (BCM communication loss)          |

### Diagnosis Table

| Step           | Finding                  |
| -------------- | ------------------------ |
| OBD scan       | No BCM response          |
| CAN resistance | 120 Ω (incorrect)        |
| Inspection     | Water in BCM connector   |
| Scope test     | CAN_L distorted waveform |

### Root Cause

| Issue                  | Result                |
| ---------------------- | --------------------- |
| Corroded BCM connector | Open termination path |

### Fix

| Action                   | Outcome                |
| ------------------------ | ---------------------- |
| Clean + replace BCM pins | Restored communication |

---

## Case Study 2: Hyundai (Intermittent CAN Dropouts)

| Parameter    | Details                          |
| ------------ | -------------------------------- |
| Vehicle type | SUV with infotainment + body CAN |
| Complaint    | Random dashboard reset           |

### Diagnostic Table

| Step          | Result                |
| ------------- | --------------------- |
| Scan tool     | Multiple U-codes      |
| Voltage check | Fluctuating 2.3–2.7 V |
| Oscilloscope  | Noise spikes on CAN_L |

### Root Cause

| Issue             | Explanation                  |
| ----------------- | ---------------------------- |
| Alternator ripple | EMI injected into CAN wiring |

### Fix

| Action                                            | Result              |
| ------------------------------------------------- | ------------------- |
| Replace alternator diode pack + re-ground harness | Stable CAN restored |

