# 5. Combined Technician Reference Summary

## A. Fast Fault Identification Table

| Symptom               | Likely Fault                 |
| --------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| No scan tool response | Power / CAN backbone failure |
| One ECU missing       | ECU internal fault           |
| Random resets         | EMI / grounding issue        |
| CAN voltage not 2.5 V | Short or bias fault          |
| Resistance not 60 Ω   | Termination issue            |

---

## B. Golden Rules of CAN Diagnosis

| Rule                                                   | Meaning                      |
| ------------------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------- |
| Always measure resistance first                        | Fastest fault detection      |
| 2.5 V idle is critical                                 | Confirms bias network health |
| Differential signal matters more than absolute voltage | Core CAN principle           |
| One faulty ECU can collapse entire network             | True in real vehicles        |
| Oscilloscope > multimeter                              | For advanced diagnosis       |

